  "chain": [
    {
      "repo": "github.com/sg-evals/rust--01f6ddf7",
      "path": "library/proc_macro/src/lib.rs",
      "symbol": "is_available"
    },
    {
      "repo": "github.com/sg-evals/rust--01f6ddf7",
      "path": "library/proc_macro/src/bridge/client.rs",
      "symbol": "is_available"
    }
  ],
  "text": "The Rust compiler and Servo browser engine share code through the `selectors` and `stylo` crates, which are maintained in the external Servo `stylo` repository (https://github.com/servo/stylo). In Servo's workspace root `Cargo.toml` (github.com/sg-evals/servo--be6a2f99/Cargo.toml), the selectors crate is declared as a workspace dependency at line 160: `selectors = { git = \"https://github.com/servo/stylo\", rev = \"3b46f3ef27eb14ca276b4bf3ff041a6c43d93827\" }`. The main style system crate `stylo` is similarly imported at line 178. Servo's various components (layout, script, shared layout) depend on these crates via workspace references.\n\nIn the Rust repository (github.com/sg-evals/rust--01f6ddf7), the `proc_macro` bridge is the key interface enabling proc macro execution. The bridge is defined in `library/proc_macro/src/bridge/mod.rs`, which serves as the internal interface for communicating between a proc_macro client (proc macro crate) and a proc_macro server (compiler front-end). This file contains the `with_api!` macro (lines 48-104) that describes the server RPC API and the `BridgeConfig` struct (lines 148-163) that manages the active connection between server and client. Supporting bridge files include `library/proc_macro/src/bridge/client.rs` (implementing client-side logic) and `library/proc_macro/src/bridge/server.rs` (implementing server-side execution).\n\nRust's testing infrastructure directly validates Servo's `selectors` crate. In `src/tools/cargotest/main.rs` (lines 72-83), a test configuration named \"servo\" is defined that clones the Servo repository and tests specifically the \"selectors\" package (line 79). The test uses a pinned commit sha: \"785a344e32db58d4e631fd3cae17fd1f29a721ab\" and is configured to test only Stylo (Servo's CSS engine that goes into Firefox) rather than all of Servo, as noted in the comment on lines 77-78. This demonstrates that while neither the Rust compiler nor Servo's components under `compiler/` or `library/` directly import the Servo `selectors` crate, Rust includes it in its cargo test suite to ensure compatibility.\n\nThe `proc_macro` bridge is critical for this integration: when Servo build scripts or proc macros execute during compilation, they use the stable `proc_macro` API, which internally relies on the bridge in `library/proc_macro/src/bridge/mod.rs` to safely serialize RPC calls between the macro expansion client and the Rust compiler server. The bridge's `with_api!` macro generates type-safe Rust APIs for both client and server sides, ensuring that macro crates (including Servo's own proc macro dependencies) can interact safely with the compiler across potentially different Rust ABI versions."
}

